# Project Conventions

## Stack

- React 18 + TypeScript (strict mode) + Vite
- Ant Design 6 (antd) for all UI — prefer antd components over custom HTML/CSS
- Axios for API calls via `src/api/http.ts`
- react-router-dom v6 for routing
- i18next + react-i18next for translations (EN, RU, HY)
- Playwright for E2E tests
- pnpm as package manager — pin exact versions (no `^`)

## File Structure

```
src/
  api/          # API client and endpoint modules
  app/          # App entry, providers, layout, routes
  components/   # Shared reusable components
  config/       # Environment config
  consts/       # Constants, enums, route definitions
  i18n/         # i18n config + locales/ (en.json, ru.json, hy.json)
  pages/        # Page components grouped by feature folder
  styles/       # Global CSS (minimal — antd handles most styling)
  types/        # Shared TypeScript interfaces and enums
  utils/        # Pure utility functions
```

## Code Style

- Use `@/` path alias for all imports from `src/`
- Named exports only (no default exports except i18n)
- `React.FC` with explicit props interfaces for components
- Arrow functions with explicit return types for utilities
- `as const` for constant objects, derive types with `typeof`
- Use `void` prefix for fire-and-forget promises
- Prettier: double quotes, semicolons, 2-space indent, trailing commas, 90-char width

## UI Rules (antd-first)

- Use antd `Typography` (Title, Paragraph, Text) instead of raw `h1`, `p` tags
- Use antd `Flex`, `Space`, `Row`/`Col` for layout instead of custom CSS
- Use antd `Result` for error/empty states (e.g., 404 page)
- Use antd `App.useApp()` for `message`/`notification` (not static imports)
- Use antd `Dropdown` with `GlobalOutlined` icon for the language switcher
- Configure antd theme via `ConfigProvider` in `AntdProvider.tsx`
- CSS modules only for what antd cannot handle (gradients, image sizing, responsive containers)
- No inline styles — use CSS modules when custom CSS is needed

## Translations (i18n)

- All user-facing text must come from translation files — never hardcode UI strings
- Translation files: `src/i18n/locales/{en,ru,hy}.json`
- Keys are nested by section: `nav.*`, `home.*`, `catalog.*`, `product.*`, `about.*`, `contact.*`, `notFound.*`, `admin.*`, `common.*`
- Use `useTranslation()` hook in components, pass `i18n.language` to locale-aware utils
- When adding new UI text, add keys to all three locale files

## API Layer

- All HTTP calls go through `src/api/http.ts` (axios-based `http<T>` generic)
- Endpoint modules in `src/api/*.api.ts` (e.g., `productsApi`, `ordersApi`)
- Types for API responses live in `src/types/`

## Types

- Shared domain types in `src/types/` (Product, Order, etc.)
- Component-local props interfaces stay in the component file
- Enums for domain values (ProductCategory, OrderStatus) in `src/types/`
